<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; DT 466E, DT 466, 530, 530E, and HT 530 Diesel Engines - Cylinder Head and Valves -
        Recondition - Valves
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s210010404.1" svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="3">
        <title>Valves</title>
        <svcsubproc id="s210010404.1.1">
            <title>Resurface Valves</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Intake valves have larger diameter head than exhaust valves.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to resurfacing valves, dress valve grinder cutting stone, using dressing stud
                    attachment to grinder.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert valve, in serviceable condition, in grinder and set to specified angle, see "
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_S210010407.xml" xrefid="t210010403">Specifications</hotlnk>
                    ."
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Grind valve face. Remove only minimum amount of material necessary to true up valve
                    face.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010441" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5368.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Grind valve face</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Measure valve face margin at four locations (90&#176; apart) with
                    <hotlnk document="eges2101_108.xml" xrefid="t210010405">Dial Caliper</hotlnk>
                    .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010442" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5199.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Measure valve face margin</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, minimum valve face margin must be maintained across entire valve
                        face. An insufficient margin will not provide proper heat dissipation and lead to valve warping
                        or breakage.
                    </para>
                </caution>
                <note>
                    <para>Intake and exhaust valve face margins are different. Replace valve if margin is less than
                        specified minimum, see "
                        <hotlnk document="eges2101_S210010407.xml" xrefid="t210010403">Specifications</hotlnk>
                        ."
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prior to resurfacing valve stem tip, dress cutting stone using dressing stud on
                    grinder.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert valve stem in grinder.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f210010443" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figeg5/eg5367.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Insert valve stem in grinder</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Resurface valve stem tip. Touch valve stem tip to cutting stone, remove only minimum of
                    material.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>When resurfacing valve stem tip, leave sufficient material so valve lever (rocker arm) does
                        not contact valve spring locks or rotators, during operation.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>Resurfacing valve stem tip provides a new wear surface for rocker arm.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">After resurfacing valves, thoroughly clean valve and valve stem.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
